node.text: A bit of fun with the ‘ABC Girls’ ceramic figurines. node.text: Located in the Rancho Palos Verdes suburb of Los Angeles, California the Rados House designed by architect Richard Neutra in 1957. node.text: Located in Espoo, Finland is the Haukilahti water tower. Designed by architect Erkko Virkkunen in 1968 the 151 ft / 46 m concrete structure is not only a municipale cistern the upper level is the Haikaranpesä restaurant and observation deck that provides a 360 degree view of the area. Photos: Risto Kamunen / Jussi Tiainen #mcmdaily #erkkovirkkunen #haukilahtiwatertower #finland🇫🇮 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Located on the Danish island of Bornholm is the Svaneke water tower. Designed by architect Jørn Utzon in 1952 (his first major commission - he would later design the Sydney Opera House) the 174 ft / 53 m Tower - whose design was inspired by Danish sea-markers (båke) - is now a protected Danish Cultural Heritage Building. Photo: Phaidon #mcmdaily #jørnutzon #båke #betonbrut #denmark🇩🇰 mcmdaily.com
